      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW BRUTUS (3) turned in a better effort at Warrnambool last start, finishing second behind No Stop Signs (25.16) in a Mix 6/7. Has the pace to be prominent. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Likely to feature again. SWEET JORDIE (2) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fourth and beaten 5 lengths (30.30) at Sandown. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. INDIAN PRINCE (8) boasts strong form at this course and distance having won two times from four starts. Placed last time (26.22) at Geelong in a Restricted WIN, finishing second and beaten half a length. Can feature in the finish. MANILA PLUTO (1) was a debut winner who looks one of the chances.",
